==English==

===Pronunciation===
*(''noun, transitive verb''): wo͞op, /wuːp/, /<tt>wu:p</tt>/ ''or'' ho͞op, /huːp/, /<tt>hu:p</tt>/
*(''intransitive verb''): wo͝op, /wʊp/, /<tt>wUp</tt>/
[[Category:English heteronyms]]

===Homophones===
*[[hoop]] (''for one pronunciation of the noun and transitive verb'')

===Etymology 1===
Middle English ''[[whopen]]'', from Old French ''[[hopper#Old French|hopper]]'', ''[[houpper]]'', originally onomatopoeic.
[[Category:Onomatopoeia]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}
[[Category:English nouns]]

#An [[exclamation]], a [[cry]], usually of [[joy]]
#A [[gasp]], characteristic of [[whooping cough]]

====Verb====
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|whoop||}}
[[Category:English verbs]]

#{{intransitive}} To make a whoop.

====Derived terms====
*[[whoop it up]]

===Etymology 2===
Corruption of [[whip]]

====Verb====
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|whoop||}}

# {{cattag|transitive|informal}} To beat, to strike.
# {{cattag|transitive|informal}} To defeat thoroughly.

====Derived terms====
*[[whoop someone's ass]]

